  <p><strong><a href="/themes/epa_theme/pattern-lab/patterns/07-pages-listing-pages-perspectives/07-pages-listing-pages-perspectives.rendered.html">Scott Mason</a></strong><br>Director<br>American Indian Environmental Office</p>
  <p>Scott Mason is Director of the United States Environmental Protection Agency’s American Indian Environmental Office. AIEO lead efforts across the agency to protect human health and the environment in Indian country. Before coming to EPA, Scott was a vice president and the executive director of federal programs at The University of Oklahoma, where he led state and federal relations for all three of the university’s campuses. Prior to joining OU, Scott served on the staff of Oklahoma Governor Mary Fallin, as well as on her gubernatorial transition team. Scott is a proud citizen and enrolled member of the Cherokee Nation and is 5th generation western Oklahoman.</p>
